# bin/

The bin/ directory contains the CLI implementation for Intent. It includes the main entry point (`intent`), shared infrastructure (`intent_helpers`, `intent_config`), core domain commands for managing steel threads and work packages, and utility scripts for project initialization, diagnostics, and documentation.

## Files

- `intent` -- Main CLI entry point and command router; handles global commands and delegates to plugins
- `intent_helpers` -- Shared helper functions (version, checksums, terminal width, error handling)
- `intent_config` -- Configuration library for JSON parsing and project root detection
- `intent_st` -- Steel thread management (create, list, show, edit, repair, organize)
- `intent_wp` -- Work package management (create, start, done, list, show)
- `intent_init` -- Initialize new Intent projects with directory structure and config.json
- `intent_treeindex` -- Generate .treeindex directory summaries using Claude; manages shadow directory
- `intent_fileindex` -- Create and manage file indexes with checkbox state tracking
- `intent_doctor` -- Configuration diagnostics and auto-fixes for Intent projects
- `intent_upgrade` -- Upgrade STP projects to Intent with backup and migration
- `intent_bootstrap` -- Initial Intent setup for first-time installations
- `intent_help` -- Command help display system and usage information
- `intent_info` -- Display Intent installation and project information
- `intent_llm` -- Manage LLM prompts, context files, and usage rules
- `intent_main` -- Legacy stp command wrapper for backward compatibility
- `intent_minimal` -- Minimal CLI wrapper for Phase 1 testing and validation
